page.title: 15 Ecology - The Canal
page.content: The banks of the canal are an unofficial nature reserve,because very few people walk there.Marlin and Spartana grass has blocked up the estuary,but provides shelter for wildlife. Mount Manisty is a mound of earth where they have dredged the canal,it forms protection for a lot of wildlife. In winter the largest collection of duck in Europe can be seen, 47000 ducks. {Foxes}on the banks of the canal are rife and the ranger has even seen a fox walking peacefully amongst the sheep. {Kestrels}are often seen hovering along the banks looking for small rodents.
